<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>gigantea</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>semibaccata</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Cleome</i> <i>isomeris</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>ericoides</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>arborescens</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>cinereum</i>, <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>dendroideus</i>, <i>Lycium</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>littoralis</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i> and <i>Suaeda</i> <i>taxifolia</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1 m and < 5 m; canopy is open to intermittent and two tiered. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Coreopsis gigantea</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Immediate coast within 2 km of the ocean, usually on steep bluffs or stable slopes.  </div>
</div>

        
